## Common Patterns

### Loading States in Views
```vue
<v-row v-if="loading">
  <v-col cols="12" class="text-center">
    <v-progress-circular indeterminate color="primary" />
  </v-col>
</v-row>
<v-row v-else-if="error">
  <v-col cols="12">
    <v-alert type="error">{{ error }}</v-alert>
  </v-col>
</v-row>
<template v-else>
  <!-- Content here -->
</template>
```

### Fetching Data on Mount
```javascript
const data = ref([]);
const loading = ref(false);
const error = ref(null);

const fetchData = async () => {
  loading.value = true;
  try {
    data.value = await fetchPlaces();
  } catch (err) {
    error.value = err.message;
  } finally {
    loading.value = false;
  }
};

onMounted(() => {
  fetchData();
});
```

### Map Markers
Use the shared teal pin marker from `modules/map/utils/markerDefinitions.js`:
```javascript
import { createTealPinMarker } from "../utils/markerDefinitions";

const marker = L.marker([lat, lng], {
  icon: createTealPinMarker(),
});
```

---

## Anti-Patterns to Avoid

1. **NO global state** - Don't add Pinia/Vuex
2. **NO axios** - Use native `fetch()`
3. **NO ESRI/ArcGIS** - Use Leaflet for maps
4. **NO Options API** - Use `<script setup>` Composition API
5. **NO console.log in production** - Remove debug statements
6. **NO hardcoded API URLs** - Use config.js or environment variables
7. **NO direct pushes** to main/uat/prod branches
8. **NO custom CSS when Vuetify has a solution** - See below

---

## Vuetify: Prefer Native Over Custom CSS

**Always use Vuetify's built-in utilities instead of writing custom CSS.** Custom CSS creates maintenance burden and may conflict with Vuetify's theming.

### Use Vuetify utility classes:
```vue
<!-- GOOD: Vuetify spacing utilities -->
<div class="pa-4 mt-2 mb-4">Content</div>

<!-- BAD: Custom CSS -->
<div class="my-custom-spacing">Content</div>
<style>.my-custom-spacing { padding: 16px; margin-top: 8px; }</style>
```

### Use Vuetify's flex utilities:
```vue
<!-- GOOD -->
<div class="d-flex justify-space-between align-center">

<!-- BAD -->
<div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;">
```

### Use Vuetify component props:
```vue
<!-- GOOD: Use component props -->
<v-card elevation="2" rounded="lg" color="grey-lighten-4">

<!-- BAD: Override with CSS -->
<v-card class="custom-card">
<style>.custom-card { box-shadow: ...; border-radius: ...; }</style>
```

### Common Vuetify utilities:
| Purpose | Vuetify Class |
|---------|---------------|
| Spacing | `pa-4`, `mt-2`, `mx-auto` |
| Flex | `d-flex`, `justify-center`, `align-center` |
| Text | `text-h4`, `text-body-1`, `text-center` |
| Colors | `bg-primary`, `text-grey-darken-1` |
| Display | `d-none`, `d-sm-block`, `d-md-flex` |
| Sizing | `fill-height`, `w-100` |

**When in doubt**, use the Vuetify MCP server to look up the correct approach

---

## Git Workflow

**Branches:**
- `main` - Development (always deployable)
- `uat` - User acceptance testing
- `prod` - Production

**Branch naming:**
- `feature/description-of-feature`
- `bugfix/description-of-fix`
- `hotfix/critical-fix-description`

**Commits:** Use conventional commits format:
- `feat: add new feature`
- `fix: resolve bug`
- `docs: update documentation`
- `refactor: restructure code`
- `chore: maintenance tasks`

---

## Testing

**Frontend:** Vitest (in `src/web/`)
```bash
npm run test        # Watch mode
npm run test:run    # Single run
```

**Backend:** Jest (in `src/api/`)
```bash
npm test            # Run all tests
npm run test:watch  # Watch mode
```

---

## When Making Changes

1. Keep changes minimal and focused
2. Don't add unnecessary dependencies
3. Follow existing patterns in the codebase
4. Update CHANGELOG.md for user-facing changes
5. Test both frontend build (`npm run build`) and backend build (`npm run build:api`)
